<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36188f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36188f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36188f"> 188(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> O&apos;Toole &amp; goose</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Oloffe Van Kortlandt bargained <font color="green">[with the Indians]</font> for <mark>so much land as a man could cover with his nether garments</mark>. Mynheer Ten Broeck wore so many breeches that they spread forth over the land until they covered the actual site of this venerable city <font color="green">[Manhattan]</font>. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 54</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: St Kevin is traditionally believed to have rejuvenated a goose belonging to King O&apos;Toole, and, as a result, was given as much land around Glendalough as the goose could cover in its flight. </mm> </dd></dl>
